public class PSStaticItemExtractor
extends PSExtractor

Extracts pieces that are not added to Rhythmyx as items. These are more web resource type things like images, stylesheets, etc

matchSourceLocation

protected boolean matchSourceLocation(String resourceId,
                                      String rootResourceId)
Determines whether the resource-id matches the source-location of the extractor's definition. The source-location is relative to the search root path of the selector definition.

Parameters:
resourceId - The resource-id of a content tree node, it is an an absolute path and may not be null or empty.
rootResourceId - The resource id of the search root in the selector definition. It may be null.
Returns:
true if resourceId is within (or under) the source-location; otherwise return false.

extractItems

public PSItemContext[] extractItems(PSItemContext item,
                                    InputStream in)
                             throws IOException
Description copied from interface: IPSItemExtractor
Performs an analysis of the supplied resource data and extracts all found instances appropriate for this plugin. Will return as many items as the count returned by IPSItemExtractor.containsInstances(com.percussion.loader.PSItemContext). If the supplied resource contains no instances, an empty array is returned. If any instances are found, the supplied resource will be the first item in the returned array.

The current implementation will only process the first item from the returned array. The rest of the items will not be processed.

Parameters:
item - the data that contains the instances, never null .
in - The stream that can be used to get the source data. The caller of this method is responsible to close this stream, but not the method itself.
Returns:
an array of extracted items, may be empty, never null .
Throws:
IOException - if error occurs during retrieving the content.
